rComments: Really great class. Not too difficult if you have a decent math background.

Tests and problem sets are moderately difficult. Easy marks with regards to participation and presentations. Felix Recio is an amazing instructor. However, the greater your mathematical background, the better you will likely do in the course. The course had a mixture of 2nd to 5th-year students with varying math backgrounds. Course average: A-
lectures are amusing and hes a pretty nice marker. Alot of the test questions were pretty much the same as questions covered in class

If you're taking MAT157 and thinking of taking this class to help you with proofs - please don't, it's not gonna help you in the slightest. Prof was okay, TA was better, both understanding. Not too much homework, tests and problem sets graded lightly, but there's only so much of them, so every mark matters. Don't recommend, unless you enjoy math.

Great prof, he really cares and genuinely wants to help you learn the material, very passionate about what hes doing. Re-explains concepts & encourages questions 138 is hard if youre not into math, but youll do well as long as you do the work & understand basic concepts. If anything, lots of resources available and prof & TA offer help too
Nice accent, good lectures. Try harder next time

If didn't do well in first year calculus but still want to study math I would strongly recommend you take his mat138 or mat329. Either of the courses will strengthen your math background for senior year math course. Prof Recio is super nice and helpful in explaining every details of the course.

The course material is interesting but the prof. makes it harder than it needs to be. Many errors from the handouts and his mistakes during the lecture cause a lot of confusion. Yet, he marks really harsh and gives no marks for trying  unless you solve the question EXACTLY how he wants it to be solved which defeats the whole purpose of the course.
The course is great, helps to really get  into math, but the prof is just Okay.
Outstanding enthusiastic prof who made this useful class very interesting.
He is very passionate about his teaching, and knows what he is doing all the time, he is a great professor!
One of the best instructors i've ever had, he's absolutely brilliant, and he presents everything in a clear manageable manner.
He was a great teacher and even a great friend. I learned everything that I needed to know about modern mathematics and the way to approach problems and challenging questions. Great Job Felix!

Professor Recio is one of those very, very talented professors who will mark you for life.  I smiled in his class by being amazed at how intelligent, humble, friendly, and willing to help students, Prof Recio was.  Prof Recio has profoundly marked me for life, as a caring, dedicated, and extremely intelligent man!!!

Professor Recio is one of the kindest and most thoughtful profs I have ever met.  He genuinely wants his students to succeed and will go to any length to help us learn.  Math was my least favourite subject, yet I looked forward to his class every day.  I truly feel inspired by Recio's enthusiasm for teaching and I wish I had more profs like him.

Made the course unnecessarily hard. The final was brutal, although the class avg was ext. low. Prob sets, waste of time, very difficult, no relevance to the material tested. I used to enjoy calculus... not anymore and it's mainly thanks to Recio who obviously doesn't care about his course or his students. I hope I pass this course because I sure don't wanna see Recio again.

Noone knows what's going on in class. He is disorganized, he jumps into things, and he CONSTANTLY makes mistakes. The problem is not with the course material; it's with the way he chose to coordinate the course. He is pathetic.

I have much admiration and respect for Professor Recio. He is a wonderful educator who, I hope, will continue to inspire and motivate his students for years to come. Thank-you for your help throughout the years.
